Something similarly occurred in Bulgaria, peasants used to smash old wooden barrels and get fancy new plastic ones last century, ones for making wine, fermenting Sauerkraut, etc. Leaves a bad plastic taste in wine. Thankfully nowadays smarter hickchuds are reverting to real wood.

It's why I am a bit annoyed when people make fun of Sol Brah for trying not to use plastic sponges in his sink or stuff like that. Materials matter a ton and trying to get rid of cheap plastic wherever possible is a noble goal. Never ever use plastic barrels for fermenting stuff.

Was surprised that this Wes Anderson scene from Moonrise Kingdom was actually inspired by the Alex Colville painting, wonderful wholesome movie and a good artist with talent for perspective, really nice when it all flows into each other like this...

Wes Anderson doesn't see it this way, but the painting is actually a bit disturbing to me, has this Medieval "insectoid" look and emphasizes how the human form is deformed into a chimera by man's instruments and machines even though it depicts an otherwise cute and happy scene...
